caption: Excellent food for an excellent price. Best palak paneer in the NW DC area. Kind and accommodating staff and quick to deliver the perfect meal to end a long day.

Great mom-and-pop restaurant.  This is my go-to for biriyani; my favorite is the lamb biriyani, but the chef’s special is also fantastic.  I will walk 45min for this biriyani!  The owner is friendly, not very conversational, but is happy to answer any questions you have.  If you are picking up, call in your order instead of using an app; they get charged by apps like GrubHub for pickup.  No indoor seating right now.  It looks like there are a couple tables outside, but I’m not sure if they are for this restaurant.
Absolutely love the food here and the staff are super nice!

I adore this place! They serve tasty meals, their menu is varied, The cook in that restaurant is a specialist, I like very much eating all their food. The dishes are consistently of high class, the service towards the guests  is efficient. I frequently visit this restaurant and I not even once was discontended. Highly recommended.
Our go-to for takeout the last five years. Everything is delicious but I always come back to the paneer makhani.
I have searched high and low for Pakistani food like this. This is absolutely the best southeast Asian food in the area. Respect.

I've walked by several times and always loved the aromas. So happy to have finally tasted this deliciousness. Best Lamb Biryani I've had had outside of Dhaka. Really tender and flavorful lamb. Bread was great and still warm upon delivery. Ample portions. Good value.
Hole in the wall, but has the best Indian food ever.

Wow wow wow!!! I've heard so much about sacrificial lamb from friends and colleagues and I must say it certainly lives up to the hype! I ordered the curry with chicken paired with white rice from here and it was the best I have ever had, hands down! The staff is incredibly friendly here as well and their service is outstanding! I have heard outstanding things about their lamb dishes and am very excited to try these on my future visits! Overall this place is outstanding and you have got to visit!
Delicious food. Great service and helpings. Favorite spot in DC!
Delicious food.
Comforting Indian food. Delicious
Delivery was so fast and the food was bomb. Definitely my new favorite Indian joint.
Testy and delicious
Best place for naan wraps in the city!
Normally great but when the order is wrong I expect them to fix it.

I am visiting from Texas and saw this place and after looking at the reviews I am so glad I did! It is a lower level small restaurant. It is not wheelchair accessible. But on the the most important part, the FOOD.  Holy cow! The gyro was soooooo good. The bread was pillowy soft, the veggies fresh and crunchy, and the meat was plentiful, flavorful, and tender. One of the best gyros I have ever eaten.  I god a salad for more veggies because it is hard to get veggies when traveling. It was a large side salad with tomatoes, lettuce, purple cabbage, and cucumbers. A good size for the price.  The baclava was a little disappointing as it was dense but not bad. The locals eat here, the food is great and the gyro wrap is worth trying for sure!
Holy $@#&, this food was amazing! The place is clearly a less than stellar looking basement remodel, but the food they are putting out is pure gold!

This site is my first choice restaurant.  Of all restaurants I know I prefere it most. I never miss an opportunity to go to visit this restaurant. when  I want to go to a decent meal, this is the place that comes straightaway to my head. good and all kinds of  food and a large list of dishes.professional team, and great ambience. Also, the charge is reasonable. I recommend this spot with no doubt.
Really delicious, and the owner was very sweet.
Worst experience ever!
Flavor is amazing here. My kids and I got 3 different dishes, shrimp, lamb, and chicken and all of it amazing! Must try! And the staff is polite and courteous.

Very tiny small size restaurant, Not much sitting space available. When comes to food it can compete  with any big Indian Pakistani cuisine. Excellent taste wonderful customer service. Street parking.
My favorite butter chicken in town

this place is a no go. they are not friendly towards people with food allergies. I spoke with someone over the phone who thought the concept itself was foreign. If you have a shellfish allergy  or wheat allergy, avoid this place. they're not patient with you on this, and will give you a hard time and act as if you are speaking non-sense.

Mr. Omar is a wonderful man who has introduced me to new flavors. This is a small business, with big flavors and bold tastes. I love the curry chicken, spinach, and chickpeas with raita. They have lunch specials before 3pm, but the price is so reasonable for this area it doesn't matter either way. The naan is made fresh and.the restaurant is clean and fresh smelling. They offer drinks as well. Can't wait to visit again.
Lamb kabob was tough and a bit dry. Only 4 chunks of meat. Not very good value at $13. Chicken tikka masala was standard or below average
The curry was watery and tasteless.

Went to this place during a business-trip to DC. The delivered food was super delicious and prices are very reasonable. We got great portions and the staff is very kind and friendly! I would definitely recommend this place!

The name of the place was the main attraction at first (we even asked why the name and the reason why is to mark that the meat is Halal). The quality of the dishes did not disappoint. I was happy with my vegetarian dish (okra or lady fingers, in a wonderful spicy mix), and my friends liked their chicken and goat (!) stews. The dal was also very good. A definite recommendation.

The Sacrificial Lamb!!! I dont know how this place doesn't have 5 stars. It's a dive but everything we tried was delicious and packed with flavor. Give the goat curry a go. Good naan and butter chicken as well. Staff is super nice, and the food was solid both for dine-in and take-out.
Great food and great service
Best gas in dc, no cap. Lamb gyro is the way to go
This is one of my favorite go to places in dc. Super fair prices, with great portions, and even better tasting food! The staff is very kind and friendly, would definitely recommend.
Love this place! Excellent prices, best naan I’ve ever had
Nice neighborhood place for Indo-pak takeout. Make sure to get some of the garlic naan - it’s really well done.
Great kabob and the naan bread was awesome

Oh my goodness this place is delicious. On our first visit (definitely not our last!) we were the only customers the man behind the counter didn't know by name and order. Everything was delicious. The palak paneer was some of the best I've ever had and the lamb korma hit the spot. However, the star of our meal was the naan. It is fluffy is the best way and deserving of the claim "best naan in DC"
I ordered only one item. They still got my order wrong...very wrong. And then they told me to ask Uber Eats for a refund. I will not be ordering from them again.

Living close by, one of my semi-weekly pleasures is getting food from here, picking it up after grocery shopping at Safeway, and taking it home to devour my faves - goat curry, lamb rogan josh, palak paneer, samosa chaat, basmati rice and a variety of naan!  This locally owned business has great and efficient service. Yes, there is limited seating indoors, but that’s because people mostly takeout. The owner is very kind.  This is the best, unpretentious food of its kind in D.C.
Ordered the lamb kabob with rice.  Got chicken and no rice, with a sad little side salad.  The chicken wasn’t even that good.
My first time trying this type of food,  ohhhh it was soooooooooo good.

There is almost no place to sit if you wanna dine in. There are like 3 mini tables with 8 chairs, that's it! Gets overcrowded if more than 4 people come in. The disposable plates they give you are either very small or they fill them way too much. The food is absolutely disappointing. I came here to eat authentic pakistani/indian food and it definitely was not. The service is okay. The overwhelming positive reviews are very misleading.
The meat was too old and hard to even eat!! So sad to have this low quality resturant in this area.

(Translated by Google) It is possible to eat in, takeaway Indian-Pakistani restaurant. Purchase Rambiriyani. The treatment of bone was bad, fragments were mixed. Pakuchi more.  (Original) イートインも可能な、持ち帰り系インド・パキスタン料理店。 ラムビリヤニを購入。 骨の処理が悪く、欠片が混ざってました。パクチー多め。
Great Pakistani and Indian takeout. Excellent service and delivery
First time having curry chicken. Not a fan of the spinach but the veggie balls were everything!!

As an Indian person that likes to cook, I often find Indian restaurants crazy over priced and overly spiced.  I ordered delivery and was impressed by the goat, very tender, as well as the lamb wrap.  Delicious and moderately priced!

I’ve tried this place a few times now, and can say confidently that it sits squarely in the realm of DC Indian places with expensive and tasty yet inauthentic Indian food. The paneer makhani was more like spaghetti sauce with cheese, the dal relatively tasteless. The chicken dishes are good but also harder to mess up. The interior of the edifice itself is tough to look at. They didn’t try to make it a nice eating environment - more of a takeaway place. The name itself Is a joke.  If you want tasty Indian style food like chicken tikka or butter chicken and don’t mind paying 14 dollars, you’ll like this place. If you’re looking for authentic Indian food home cooking style, you won’t find it here.
Great food! Are you kidding me with bad reviews. Ok here’s a hint, if they can’t spell It’s a great indicator that they’ve no taste... you can tell when it’s not a typo. Yum yum yum is my review.

Maybe we just ordered the wrong things.  It was truly the worst Indian food we have ever had.  The beef was inedible it was so tough.  The chicken tika masala was super bland.  I don't write many reviews for restaurants... only the occasional "wow! that was fantastic" or "Gosh, that was horrible."  This was the latter.
Great food and service!

What a disappointment.  I ordered from Sacrificial Lamb through Eat24. The food was barely warm. It’s 4 minutes by car or 3 minutes by bike from the restaurant to the hotel I was at. I really like Indian Butter Chicken but not from this restaurant. The Butter Chicken from Sacrificial Lamb had no taste to it. It looked the right color, I don’t know where the flavor was hiding. The texture was right for chicken but it was horribly bland. I ordered Garlic Naan and Kashmiri Naan, both room temperature and lacking taste. The real insult was the $2.95 Rass Malai. I thought it was a small cup with some type of condiments at first. It was a portion for a Hobbit with a gastric bypass, it was gone in two wanting bites. I wouldn’t recommend eating at this restaurant.  This is probably my most negative review on Yelp.

Don’t let the name scare you away...this place is an absolute gem! I went for lunch during a busy work day. My food was prepared quickly and the perfect temperature when it was delivered to my table. I was a little nervous about the sauces on the chicken wrap as I’m usually not a big fan of cilantro but I took the advice of the gentleman who took my order and was blown away. The chicken was tender and well seasoned which complemented the house sauce that was on the wrap. Everything tasted very fresh and was the perfect amount of food for lunch. Not too heavy and not so light that I’ll need to eat again in an hour. I will definitely be back.
Friendly people, was the food was good. I asked for a Spicy shrimp Briyani and was not disappointed at all. loved it.
Good one.
It's amazing care out for neighbours and community.
Terrible
I tried their combo kabab. It was dry and overcooked, not fresh. The sitting place is really tiny and pact. Not a recommended place to have good meal.

"Blend" is the word to describe this place, the taste, the take-out ambience, the dishes available on the menu only hint to one thing - lacking depth of flavor ... If you're looking for a quick meal with some ethnic touch, look elsewhere in the neighborhood, like Chicken +  Whiskey on 14th or Triple B Fresh at DuPont Circle. Sorry I won't be back.

Delicious! I tried the tomato soup, the goat saag, and mango lassi. I liked it all! The goat was really tender... Just too many bones in it for my liking (it was a little messy to eat). However, I know they keep the bones in for flavor. The soup also had a good flavor and a generous portion for a few bucks. And they deliver for free on GrubHub. I recommend it if you're staying downtown DC.
The food &the service is great. My advice is do it carry away.
Delicious & great pricing!
Nice food

I don't know what people are talking about regarding portion sizes... for the price it is more than enough. The food was pretty good, we were visiting DC from NY  for New Year's, must say I wasn't disappointed. One advice for the owner/chef, with the appetizers, you guy should also provide the tamarind chutney (brown sauce) not just the chili/mint chutney by itself (green chutney). Tandoori chicken was very flavorful and the biryani portions were plentiful. Def worth the price.
Across from my office and a great spot to pick lunch up from!  I love the tomato soup.
fill up spot!
Just moved from NYC to DC and was looking for a good Indian place. This is it! The food was excellent, authentic, and well priced. I highly recommend.
(Translated by Google) Excellent  (Original) ممتاز
Great food!! :)
It's a little hole in the wall but the food and service were great. Halal food served.
Fantastic food and good conversation.
Love this place. Simple and sincere. No gimmicks, just good food and nice people.

Excellent variety, very flavorful, good value for the price. Fellow at the counter was very kind. Highly recommend, especially for vegetarian options! Outside seating made this a lovely and relaxing lunch spot.
Had the buttered chicken, it was cooked to perfection. The garlic naan was made to order and was also fantastic. Definitely will be back.
Delicious hole in the wall south Asian food. Excellent, courteous service. In an age of chain stores and impersonality, they remember who you are.

Good place to grab some Indian takeout. The place is tiny but does have seating if you wish to dine in. Went in with a group of 5 all getting orders to-go and it only took about 10 minutes for all of the food to be bagged up and ready to leave with.
Food with Great flavor

A little restaurant hidden on R st in the middle of DC. They have a variety of vegeterian foods, but also great chicken and goat meat. The food is prepared in front of you and their stuff is moderately priced and halal.
Tasty and fast. Staff was great.
Tasty north Indian food available but the seating capacity is very less, they hardly have 4-5 tables.
Very nice and delicious

Absolute waste of money. Portions are extremely small compared to price. The food was served in like 2 minutes and the kabob was not ever fresh made...it was just some they had prepared long ago and heated it up to serve. The taste is also average...even i can cook better chik peas than this place. Not recommended
The curries were great and just what we needed. The shop is a little old, however the food is great.
Tasty! We love the Buttered Chicken, Samosas, Chickpeas, and Garlic Naan

The portions are for tiny, tiny, tiny people, especially compared to the price. The palak paneer was the best thing in our order by far. The butter chicken is just not cooked correctly, and so was the grilled chicken kabob. The chickpea side was pretty good. A very underwhelming experience on a hungry night. Definitely not worth the $40 for 3 tiny dishes.

Counter/order and sit type place. Very nice staff that's willing to make your dish to your liking. Sat outside on the patio and they even brought us extra nan. Defiantly tasty and good selection of dishes.
Good butter chicken. Wraps are a bit overpriced.
Try the Mango Lassi, so creamy and decadent.

Was there last year and the food was amazing. The restaurant is not what we are used to in Europe, it's not that it was dirty or something but it does need some attention.  Anyway, if ever again in DC it would be the first place to visit, even before the White House :)
The place is a little sketchy but the food is outstanding and so is the customer service. The naan is also delicious.

Excellent food at reasonable prices. The employees are friendly, courteous and accommodating. I subtract one star because I am comparing the food with "gourmet" Indian cuisine I've enjoyed elsewhere. The employees are a true "melting pot."
Great takeout joint. Classic hole in the wall.
Very yummy Indian takeout, but beware. Delivery times (even if you're in the neighborhood) tend to be much longer than quoted.
The bread is really nice and the food is really bad and the smell food is fresh is amazing it's great service and very nice location

The food was decent, but it doesn't even begin to outweigh the two hour wait and the horrible customer service. I called my order in at 8:38pm with someone who informed me that my single question about a side was unimportant because he was in a rush without answering my single question. Yet, I still placed an order for two entrees. After an hour and 45 minutes I called for an update/cancel of my order. I was told the delivery guy was 5 minutes away. 7 minutes later I called back to cancel my order and after a couple minutes on the phone the delivery guy showed up. I accepted the delivery. When I got inside it was lukewarm, if not colder than room temperature, and it had to be microwaved to be eaten. I live within a couple blocks of the restaurant. The food should not need microwaving, and should not take two hours to arrive. I enjoyed the decent food (I've had similar quality food from trader Joe's frozen foods without the ridiculous wait) but the overall experience was not worth the $30 it cost. I will never order from them again, and I will consider any other restaurant a better option than them. I want to make it clear because when I read some reviews of businesses, some seem to be outliers or almost obsessive reviews and indicative of a potentially unhinged reviewer. I am not a chronic reviewer nor a critical customer. Just treat me decent and give me decent product and service, and I will happily enjoy the decent experience. This interaction was so thoroughly negative, I felt the need to review the business. Please, do yourself a favor and enjoy food from elsewhere.
Hole in the wall, limited menu but good food. The special with butter chicken and 2 sides plus naan (very well made) is a great takeout deal.
The food here is consistently terrific, and the owners and staff are wonderful people. Highly recommended.
Great takeout in a pinch. I had a roommate that would order from here twice a week and I can understand why. The grilled chicken naan wrap is a great standby and the platters aren't bad either.
Super tasty Indian!

I've stopped by Sacrificial Lamb twice on my walk home after work to order their Butter Chicken plate, which includes two sides (I like the spinach and chickpeas), rice and naan. Their naan is delicious and the staff here are incredibly friendly and helpful! I'd never consider eating in this subterranean-level place, but it's great for a quick pick up when you're famished and don't feel like cooking at home.
Fantastic.  Nice n fresh food. Nice customers care people.

I've only had the butter chicken (amazing) and naan (perfect). For a relatively low price point, I've loved this food and so have all my friends. It won't change your world and don't use it to impress a date, but it's a great contribution to the neighborhood.
Very tasty!
One of the best restaurants in the area. Food is alittle spicy but excellent. Worth every penny. Very nice

Unassuming shop with a sunken entrance one flight down from street level next to a dry cleaner. I pass it frequently but never when I was hungry until recently. Very glad I stopped in, portions were the right size, breads were baked after we ordered them in front of us and the food was excellent! It will definitely be on my list for inexpensive eats in the future!
